Chloris virgata

   [683.jpg]
   Authority Sw.
   Family Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
   Synonyms
   Common names feather top Rhodes grass, feather-top chloris, feather
   fingergrass, showy chloris, capim de raiz, capim mimoso de cacho,
   witpluim chloris
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 683

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A variable grass with culms up to 15-90 cm high,
   often decumbent and rooting from the lower nodes. USES Used for pasture
   and makes a somewhat inferior hay. It is one of the first grasses to
   colonize bare ground, and has been used for reseeding denuded
   rangeland. GROWING PERIOD Summer-growing annual grass. COMMON NAMES
   Feather finger grass, Woolly-top Rhodes grass, Feather-top Rhodes
   grass, Black-seed, Feather-top chloris. FURTHER INF Feather finger
   grass can be found at elevations between sea level and 2000 m. It is
   often found along roadsides, in grasslands as a weed and is secondary
   in cultivation. It can become a weed in cultivated fields.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 293-295 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, SAL, PH, LIG]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 11 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 511 [USE]
   Ibrahim K 1987 pp 105
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 87 [RAIN, TEXT]

